  "instructions": [
    "Combine rice and water in a large saucepan, and bring to a boil over high heat.",
    "Reduce heat to low and cover with a tight-fitting lid, then transfer saucepan to a bain-marie or a large bowl over a pot of simmering water.",
    "Cook for 15-20 minutes, or until rice is tender and water has been absorbed.",
    "Remove saucepan from heat and stir in butter, jam, toasted almonds, sea salt, and black pepper.",
    "Garnish with fresh rosemary leaves and serve warm."
